      "comment": "OFF YOUR FACESKI (8) has been racking up the wins, making it five in succession when he worked to the front and dug deep to score by a head last time out, taking his strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. Won from this row last month and draws for a trail with the sprint lane in play. Could extended the winning streak. TE AMO (1) missed narrowly two back at Cranbourne before a fourth at his latest appearance at Melton. Has had eight weeks off since but was kept up to the mark with a trial and is well served by the ace draw. KENNYWOULD (6) was dominant in coming from the back row for a last-start win by 12 metres at Kilmore. This is stronger but his other two career wins came at this shorter distance. DELS DESTINY NZ (5) has been about the mark of late and must be respected.",
